AN ACT relating to gaming; revising provisions relating to the
operation of a gaming salon; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Nevada Gaming Commission, with the advice and
2 assistance of the Nevada Gaming Control Board, to adopt regulations governing the
3 standards of operation for a gaming salon, including the policies and procedures
4 governing certain games which may be offered in a gaming salon. Existing law
5 further provides that such regulations: (1) must require a gaming salon to include
6 table games; (2) may authorize a gaming salon to include slot machines; and (3)
7 must require minimum wagers of $500 for slot machines in a gaming salon. (NRS
8 463.4073) This bill authorizes the regulations governing the standards of operation
9 for a gaming salon to allow for table games, slot machines or other gambling
10 games, or any combination thereof. This bill also requires the regulations to provide
11 that the minimum wagers for slot machines in a gaming salon must be established
12 by the licensee and approved by the Board.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
